While ANC leaders are in mourning, they're also attending a crucial NEC Lekgotla. The meeting is being held virtually and will debate how to pay for COVID-19 vaccines, deal with rampant corruption and the economy.#DStv403 #eNCA eNCA's Govan Whittles reports. JOHANNESBURG - While ANC leaders mourn the passing of Minister in the Presidency, Jackson Mthembu, they are also attending a crucial NEC Lekgotla. The meeting is being held virtually and will debate how to pay for COVID-19 vaccines, deal with rampant corruption and the economy. READ: COVID-19 vaccine funding will not be a problem, says Ramaphosa President Cyril Ramaphosa says paying for COVID-19 vaccines won’t be a problem – but the pressure is building. “The country needs to be safe in the knowledge that the government is doing everything in its power, to bring the vaccines to our shores," said ANC secretary-general, Jessie Duarte. Watch the video above for more details on this story.